  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether an intensive, eight session behavioral
      intervention is superior to standard care in achieving abstinence from cigarettes in smokers
      living with HIV/AIDS.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
